<section id="head-wrapper">
  <section id="homepage-top">
    <header id="page-header" class="primary">
      <h1>Get better, faster in our small, hands-on workshops</h1>
    </header>

    <section id="workshop-list">
      <% if @audiences.empty? %>
        <p id="no-courses">No courses are running at this time.</p>
      <% else %>
        <% @audiences.each do |audience| %>
          <% if audience.courses.only_public.any? %>
            <h2><%= audience.name %></h2>
            <ul>
              <%= render audience.courses.only_public %>
            </ul>
          <% end %>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
    </section>

    <aside class="first">
      <h2><a href="/backbone-js-on-rails"><%= t ".backbone_ebook_header", :default => "Backbone.js on Rails eBook" %></a></h2>
      <p><%= t ".backbone_ebook_description", :default => "Learn how to build snappier, more interactive apps with cleaner code and better tests in less time." %></p>
    </aside>

    <aside>
      <h2><a href="/vim"><%= t ".vim_header", :default => "Vim for Rails Developers Screencast" %></a></h2>
      <p><%= t ".vim_description", :default => "Create and edit your Ruby on Rails code more efficiently." %></p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</section>

<section id="more-information">
  <section id="more-information-wrapper">
    <section id="class-photos">
      <ul>
        <li class="first"><%= image_tag("/images/public/class-photo-3.jpg", :alt => "thoughtbot training" )%></li>
        <li class="center"><%= image_tag("/images/public/class-photo-2.jpg", :alt => "thoughtbot training" )%></li>
        <li class="last"><%= image_tag("/images/public/class-photo-1.jpg", :alt => "thoughtbot training" )%></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="why-love">
      <%= t(".why-love", :default => "<ul>
        <li><strong>Real life skills</strong> Our instructors build sites every day using the technology and skills we teach in our workshops. We focus on the things you need to know when doing real work.</li>
        <li><strong>Human touch</strong> We keep our workshops small, so there&rsquo;s always someone ready to answer your questions. We also provide a delicious group lunch, a great chance to get to know your classmates and the <a href=\"http://thoughtbot.com/about/\">thoughtbot team</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>A beautiful office</strong> Our workshops are run in our newly renovated office, in a comfortable, spacious room, with a great view of the Common in downtown Boston.</li>
      </ul>") %>
    </section>

    <section id="testimonials">
      <section id="column-1">
        <q>After the training session my code style is so fresh, Vogue wants to publish my tests.</q>
        <p class="source">&mdash;<a href="http://gregsterndale.com/">Greg Sterndale</a></p>

        <q>There is no Intro to Rails book out there currently (I have tried quite a few) that can provide you with the same amount of knowledge that you can pickup in the two day thoughtbot Intro to Rails workshop.</q>
        <p class="source">&mdash;<a href="http://twitter.com/richrines">Rich Rines</a></p>
      </section>

      <section id="column-2">
        <q>Cannot recommend Design for Developers more. It&rsquo;s amazing and I have a totally different outlook on design and web development.</q>
        <p class="source">&mdash;<a href="http://chuckvose.com/">Chuck Vose</a></p>

        <q>Having taken a thoughtbot training class on my own dime I can say it&rsquo;s 110% worth it. If you can hook it up, do it.</q>
        <p class="source">&mdash;<a href="http://joeloliveira.com/">Joel Oliveira</a></p>
      </section>
    </section>
  </section>
</section>
